ref: Jour: Canadian Journal of Physics, Vol.46, p.1974 (1968)
title: The anisotropy of fast photoneutrons from chromium.

x4freetext: The anisotropy of fast photoneutrons from chromium.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Canadian Journal of Physics, Vol.46, p.1974 (1968)

x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Toronto, Toronto, Ontario, Canada
Univ. of Toronto, Toronto, Ontario, Canada

x4freetext: The variations of anisotropy  with  energy  of
photoneutrons from chromium is explained in terms of
single-particle transitions from different shells.
Energy spectra of photoneutrons from  chromium
are    compared   with   calculations   within   the
evaporation model.
The anisotropy of fast  photoneutrons  from  chromium
and   lead  has  been  measured  as  a  function  of
bremsstrahlung energy in the region  22-32  MeV.  In
the  case  of chromium the anisotropy increases with
energy. A possible explanation for this is advanced,
and   the   implications  of  this  explanation  are
compared with results from other nuclei.

x4freetext: The details   of   the   experimental   method    of
measurements of angular distributions.
Data were compiled in  SCJAD  of  Saratov
State University.
Corrected by V.Varlamov, V.Mclane.
Corrected by SD and VV:  Updated  to  new
date formats,  lower case,  small corrections in all
SUBENTs, REACTION, SUBENT 010 deleted because no data
for EXFOR.
Corrected by V.Varlamov: METHOD deleted
and ANALYSIS added in SUBENTs 001-006.
For the range of bremsstrahlung energies only
one or two of many possible particle transitions
result in neutron whose energy exceeds 5 or 6 MeV.
The effective threshold energy for the Si(n,p)
reaction was used as the neutron detector.
The 1.78-MeV gamma  rays  emitted  after  the
beta-decay  of  Al-28  produced  by  the  Si-28(n,p)
reaction  serve  as  a  measure  of   fast   neutron
intensity.
Si-28 threshold detector.
Statistical errors are presented.
Data from Table I of CJP,46,1974,1968.

DATA-ERR -> ERR-S, REACTION: BRS -> BRA.
